<span class="header1">COMMUNICATIONS</span>
<p>Your ability to communicate may be your ticket into the
occupations in this field. Those who work in this field are
excellent communicators. They can speak in front of a large group of
people.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Public Relations
Specialist</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/1369.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Public Relations
Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Companies want customers and others to see them
in a positive way.  So they hire people to see that this happens.
As a public relations specialist, you would let people know about
the good things your company has done.  To do this, you would write
press releases, brochures, and television and radio announcements.
It would be important that you were enthusiastic about the company.
You would also need to be able to write and speak
clearly.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Opportunities should be best for college
graduates who combine a degree in public relations, journalism, or
another communications-related field with a public relations
internship or other related work experience.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of public relations
specialists was $61,150 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Technical Writer</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/43289.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Technical Writer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Have you ever read the owner's manual for your
computer, sound system, or video game? The person who wrote the
manuals was a technical writer. In this job, you would write
manuals, catalogs, and instruction books.  You would make science or
technical information and directions easy for others to
understand.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Most jobs in this occupation require a college
degree preferably in communications, journalism, or English, but a
degree in a technical subject may also be useful for technical writing
positions. For example, writers who work on computer manuals usually
have a degree in computer science.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of technical writers was
$72,850 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Actor/Actress</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/C575061.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Actor/Actress" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you have a burning desire to be in the movies
or in a play on Broadway, you might become a professional actor or
actress.  In this job, you would play the role of a character in a
play, television program, or movie.  To be successful, you must have
a talent for acting.  You must also be able to perform in front of a
large group of people. You would have to be able to remember your
lines.  You would also have to get along with other actors, the
directors, and others who make the production possible.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Formal dramatic training, either through an
acting conservatory or a university program, generally is necessary
for these jobs, but some people successfully enter the field without
it. </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median wage of actors/actresses was $20.43 per hour in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header1">CREATIVE TECHNOLOGY</span>
<p>The occupations in this field need people who can use their
technical skills to create something new. Your creativity and
interest in technology will help you to succeed in this field.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Photographer</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/43060.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Photographer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like taking pictures and have a
good "eye," you might become a professional photographer. A
photographer combines communications skills and technology.  In this
job, you would take pictures of people, things, or events. You must
be creative.  Your goal is to show people something they might
otherwise not have seen.  You must understand the technical aspects
of the camera.  You must also know how to produce finished images and prints using computer software. Many photographers work for themselves. So, it is helpful to understand
how a small business works.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A bachelor's degree in photography or the visual
arts can develop your basic skills.  But, you also need to be
creative to succeed in this field.  Spend as much time as possible
looking at great pictures and taking your own. Getting involved in
photography clubs and working in photo shops and labs will help you
learn more about using your camera to capture successful
photographs.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of photographers was
$36,280 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Video Editor</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/C506027.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Video Editor" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>When you watch a movie or television program,
you are watching more than the work of actors.  You are watching the
work of a video editor, too.  As a video editor, you would use your
creativity to piece together the footage of a film or program. You
would have two goals.  You would want to be sure the audience could
understand the story.  You also want to edit the film so that the
audience could "feel" the movie.  You would use video equipment to
make the movie seems exciting, dramatic, funny, or scary.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Television, video, and motion picture camera
operators and editors usually acquire their skills through formal
postsecondary training at vocational schools, colleges,
universities, or photographic institutes. A bachelor's degree may be
required for some positions, particularly those for film and video
editors. Employers usually seek applicants with a good eye,
imagination, and creativity, as well as a good technical
understanding of how the camera operates. </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of video editors was
$63,780 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Desktop Publisher</span><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Desktop publishers use computer software to
design page layouts for newspapers, books, brochures, and other
items that will be printed or put online. They collect the text,
graphics, and other materials they will need and then format them
into a finished product.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>On-the-job training is provided for employees. Many desktop 
publishers need an associate's degree.
</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of desktop publishers was
$45,390 in May 2019. </blockquote>

