<span class="header1">TECHNOLOGY</span>
<p>If you prefer a hands-on approach in your work, you might be
interested in occupations in this field.  You need to have skill in
using technology.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Lighting Designer</span><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A lighting designer is a part of the set design stage crew
that helps the actors look better on stage.  If you would like to be
a part of a drama production, but not want to be an actor or
director, this may be a job for you.  As a lighting designer, you
would use your technical know-how to make the lighting on stage
reflect the "feeling" of the play. For example, if the scene were
set in the middle of an electrical storm you would make sure there
were flashes of light on stage.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A bachelor's degree may help you to get a job,
but it is not required.  It is important to have experience.
Sometimes, lighting designers serve as an apprentice before becoming
a designer. An apprentice is someone who is learning a trade by
working on the job with an experienced person.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of lighting designers was $54,600
in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Sound Engineering
Technician</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/43158.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Sound Mixer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Sound engineering technicians operate machines
and equipment to record, synchronize, mix, or reproduce music,
voices, or sound effects in recording studios, sporting arenas,
theater productions, or movie and video productions.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>The best way to prepare for a broadcast and
sound engineering technician job is to obtain technical school,
community college, or college training in broadcast technology,
electronics, or computer networking.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of  sound engineering
technicians was $45,510 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />


	<span class="header2">Road Manager</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BF/43239.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Road Manager" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>When rock bands or stage productions take their
shows on the road, they hire a road manager. If you became a road
manager, you would make the arrangements for equipment and
performers to arrive at the concerts or performances on time. Road
managers have a tough job.  They are expected to deal with any
problems during a tour and to handle a thousand details.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>There is no college degree needed to be a road
manager. You must have experience working with people and solving
problems.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>According to the job search website, indeed.com, the median annual wage of road managers was $40,952 in September 2020. </blockquote>

